# Musical Markdown (.mmd) — Example: Jazz Turnaround
#
# "Midnight Changes" — 8 measures of a standard ii–V–I–VI turnaround in C,
# scored for melody, comping hand, and walking bass.
#
# What this demonstrates:
#   - Extended jazz chord voicings: Dm7, G7, Cmaj7, A7 as four-note []-chords
#   - Explicit accidentals inside chords: C#3 (A7 major 3rd), Bb2 (bass passing tone)
#   - Sub-beat comp rhythm: R/8,[chord]/8 places the chord on the "and" of a beat
#   - Walking bass: chromatic approach tones (Bb2, B2) connecting chord roots
#   - C-track carrying lead-sheet chord symbols aligned to the beat grid
#   - Arpeggio modifier (arp) on the Cmaj7 downbeat, beat-2 comp
#
# Note: .mmd rhythms are exact — not swing. Apply swing quantization in your
# DAW or sequencer after MIDI export for an authentic jazz feel.
#
# Chord progression (repeating 4-bar turnaround, played twice):
#   Dm7  |  G7  |  Cmaj7  |  A7  |
#    ii  |   V  |    I    |  VI7 |  (→ loops back to ii)
#
# Run:
#   python tools/mmd_validator.py   examples/jazz-turnaround.mmd
#   python tools/mmd_to_midi.py     examples/jazz-turnaround.mmd
#   python tools/mmd_to_lilypond.py examples/jazz-turnaround.mmd
#   python tools/mmd_transposer.py  examples/jazz-turnaround.mmd --transpose +2

@TITLE: Midnight Changes
@BPM: 132
@TIME: 4/4
@KEY: C
@TRACKS: T1=Melody, T2=Comp, T3=Bass

[CLEF:T1:treble]
[CLEF:T2:bass]
[CLEF:T3:bass]

[DYN:mf]

# ── C1: Chord symbols (lead-sheet annotations) ────────────────────────────────
# C-tracks carry text labels synchronized to the beat grid.
# The symbol occupies beat 1; empty slots fill the remaining beats.

C1: Dm7;  ; ; | Dm7;   ; ; | G7;    ; ; | G7;    ; ; |
  | Cmaj7; ; ; | Cmaj7; ; ; | A7;    ; ; | A7;    ; ; |.

# ── T1: Melody ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Quarter-note bebop melody targeting chord tones on strong beats.
# Half notes in even-numbered measures create phrase breathing room.
#   M1/M2: Dm7 — opens on the 5th (A4), resolves through F4 (3rd) to D4 root
#   M3/M4: G7  — F4 (7th) to B4 (3rd) signals the dominant tritone
#   M5/M6: Cmaj7 — ascending arpeggio, returns to 3rd (E4) at phrase end
#   M7/M8: A7  — stepwise descent from E5 lands on A4 root to close

T1: A4/4; C5/4; F4/4; E4/4 | D4/2;  ;      G4/4; A4/4 |
  | F4/4; B4/4; D5/4; C5/4 | B4/2;  ;      A4/4; G4/4 |
  | E4/4; G4/4; B4/4; D5/4 | C5/2;  ;      G4/4; E4/4 |
  | A4/4; G4/4; C#5/4; E5/4 | D5/4; C#5/4; A4/2;      |.

# ── T2: Comping (shell voicings) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Shell voicings: root + 3rd + 5th + 7th. Two patterns alternate:
#
#   Odd measures  (M1,M3,M5,M7): R/4 ; chord/4 ; R/4 ; R/8,chord/8
#   Even measures (M2,M4,M6,M8): chord/4 ; R/4 ; R/4 ; R/8,chord/8
#
# The R/8,[voicing]/8 in beat 4 places the chord on the "and-of-4" —
# a jazz anticipation that pushes harmonically into the next downbeat.
# See spec §8.2: comma separates sub-beat events within one beat slot.
#
# Chord voicings:
#   Dm7:   [D3,F3,A3,C4]   root · min3 · 5th · min7
#   G7:    [G2,F3,B3,D4]   root · min7(F) · maj3(B) · 5th  ← F↔B tritone
#   Cmaj7: [C3,E3,G3,B3]   root · maj3 · 5th · maj7
#   A7:    [A2,C#3,E3,G3]  root · maj3(C#) · 5th · min7   ← C# explicit

T2: R/4; [D3,F3,A3,C4]/4;            R/4; R/8,[D3,F3,A3,C4]/8 |
  | [D3,F3,A3,C4]/4;            R/4; R/4; R/8,[D3,F3,A3,C4]/8 |
  | R/4; [G2,F3,B3,D4]/4;            R/4; R/8,[G2,F3,B3,D4]/8 |
  | [G2,F3,B3,D4]/4;            R/4; R/4; R/8,[G2,F3,B3,D4]/8 |
  | R/4; [C3,E3,G3,B3]/4(arp);       R/4; R/8,[C3,E3,G3,B3]/8 |
  | [C3,E3,G3,B3]/4;            R/4; R/4; R/8,[C3,E3,G3,B3]/8 |
  | R/4; [A2,C#3,E3,G3]/4;           R/4; R/8,[A2,C#3,E3,G3]/8 |
  | [A2,C#3,E3,G3]/4;           R/4; R/4; R/8,[A2,C#3,E3,G3]/8 |.

# ── T3: Walking Bass ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# One quarter note per beat — the jazz "walking" pattern.
# Each measure's final note approaches the next chord's root:
#   M1 (Dm7): ...G2  —  root of G7 = same note, direct arrival
#   M2 (Dm7): ...G2  —  leads into M3 G7 root
#   M4 (G7):  ...Bb2→B2  —  chromatic half-step up to C3 (Cmaj7 root)
#   M6 (Cmaj7): ...Bb2→A2 — chromatic descent to A7 root
#   M8 (A7): ...C3→D3  — stepwise approach back toward Dm7

T3: D2/4; F2/4; A2/4; G2/4  | D2/4; E2/4; F2/4;  G2/4  |
  | G2/4; B2/4; D3/4; F3/4  | G2/4; A2/4; Bb2/4; B2/4  |
  | C3/4; E3/4; G3/4; B3/4  | C3/4; B2/4; Bb2/4; A2/4  |
  | A2/4; C#3/4; E3/4; G3/4 | A2/4; B2/4; C3/4;  D3/4  |.
